This paper is primarily focused on the mathematical theory of cooperative communication, which is a central topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the statistical problem solved in cooperation, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the theory for human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
